			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Macro Madness  =P<a name="23623"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 4:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hola;
<br />

<br />
Fairly happy new N52 user here.
<br />

<br />
1). haven't seen that.
<br />

<br />
2). Make a &quot;stopsong&quot; hotkey button and use that instead of hitting the song button again to stop it.  i.e. use alt-# to cast, put in a delay, then hit the hotkey button for stopsong to stop it.  If you remap the hotkey button to use a F-button and alt, you'll be able to type normally while twisting as well.
<br />

<br />
3). interested in that as well, I only use it for non-critical twists at the moment.
<br />

<br />
4). think missed notes are a function of instrument skill, not stats?  A correctly set up macro should keep going, and renew the missed note the next spin thru.
<br />

<br />
5). I think there's a programmable stop macro function in the keypad config software, so you can break a macro in the middle... haven't messed with that yet.
<br />

<br />
Also- I've read in numerous places that keypad type macros are totally &quot;legal&quot; as long as you are at the keyboard while they are running- anyone have a link to where that was stated officially tho?  I personally don't and won't abuse it, but it'd be nice to have the horse's mouth quote and the exact verbage/intent comprehended.
<br />

<br />
RdT and/or TdB</span></td>
