				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Macro Madness  =P<a name="23928"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 6:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yup,
<br />

<br />
1.
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast #
<br />

<br />
(# being any from 1 to 8 to map your song line into keybord)
<br />

<br />
You can use 9 and 0 for Inc. Msgs or /Assist %T (for whenever you are not pulling) or for whatever. 
<br />

<br />
There are 10 banks for hotkeys with 10 slots in each of them, thus 100 different macros. It can get very creative (adding groupsay for Mez song, etc).
<br />

<br />
But for twisting songs there is only... 1.
<br />

<br />
It's up to you to choose what songs you have memmed and if you want to twist 1,2,3,4 or 2,3,4,5 or 5,6,7,8 or whatevers. I do 2,3,4,5 because I always have Mez on 1, and use ~ for Toggle.
<br />

<br />
Nilufer.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
