				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Macro Madness  =P<a name="24067"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 11:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We bards are creatures of comfort. . . and as such our &quot;Twisting&quot; styles reflect what is most comfortable to us.  Whether it be the &quot;Traditional&quot; 11,22,33,44,11,22. .etc or the &quot;New Age&quot; Pad doo-hickey.  
<br />

<br />
Personally, I use a combination of Tradition and Macro'ing.  I will be twisting away at a mob 22, 33, 44, 55, 66 but I have &quot;Mezz&quot; set to a macro
<br />

<br />
/Stop song
<br />
/g Mezzing %t -- ALERT! -- Mezzing %t -- ALERT
<br />
/cast 1
<br />

<br />
As I want that message to get to the group without missing a beat.
<br />

<br />
Remember the bard is a Jack of All Trades and master of none.  So the &quot;REAL&quot; bard uses everything and is open to those new or old ideas that fit him/her.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
